has been stripped from her.

01:30.406 --> 01:31.806
I'm sorry.

01:31.839 --> 01:33.642
You have such a beautiful voice.

01:33.675 --> 01:35.978
I can't wait to hear it
when you're older.

01:36.011 --> 01:38.314
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: Will this place
have scuba diving?

01:38.347 --> 01:40.883
How old does a child have to be
to do scuba diving?

01:40.916 --> 01:42.752
I don't know, Trent.

01:42.785 --> 01:44.220
I think you're a bit too young.

01:44.252 --> 01:45.421
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>:
You're a baby.

01:45.454 --> 01:47.223
You said five minutes.

01:47.255 --> 01:49.224
Technically, it's been way,
way more than five minutes.

01:49.258 --> 01:50.660
Are we close?

01:50.693 --> 01:53.396
Stop wishing away this moment.

01:53.428 --> 01:56.165
Look out the window.
Look how pretty it is.

01:57.466 --> 01:59.101
GUY: <font color="#87CEFA">(whispers)</font>
Prisca.

01:59.133 --> 02:00.436
<font color="#87CEFA">(cell phone buttons
continue clicking)</font>

02:00.469 --> 02:01.836
Work stuff?

02:01.869 --> 02:03.773
Yeah.

02:03.806 --> 02:06.142
- Lead by actions, Mom.
- <font color="#87CEFA">(sighs)</font>

02:10.479 --> 02:12.515
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

02:16.385 --> 02:17.987
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
Wow.

02:18.020 --> 02:20.657
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>: This is
much better than Cancún.

02:28.563 --> 02:30.598
Mr. and Mrs. Capa,

02:30.631 --> 02:32.867
welcome to our version
of paradise.

02:32.901 --> 02:34.369
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: Wow.
- <font color="#87CEFA">(Prisca chuckles)</font>

02:34.402 --> 02:35.937
Hello.

02:35.970 --> 02:38.574
("To Reo iti Maru"
by Mila playing)

02:40.041 --> 02:42.478
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MANAGER</b></font>: So, this is Madrid.
She'll take care of you.

02:42.510 --> 02:45.213
From your food and beverage
preferences you selected,

02:45.247 --> 02:47.650
we've made you cocktails
to welcome you.

02:47.682 --> 02:49.284
Wow.

02:49.318 --> 02:50.853
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: Thank you.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>: Thank you.

02:50.885 --> 02:53.823
Look how big you guys are.

02:53.855 --> 02:56.157
We have a drink fountain
for you two.

02:56.190 --> 02:57.492
Can we go?

02:57.526 --> 02:58.728
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>: Mm.
- Yeah.

02:58.760 --> 03:00.362
Let's go. Let's go.

03:02.331 --> 03:05.034
Can you believe
I found this online?

03:08.736 --> 03:10.705
<font color="#87CEFA">(indistinct chatter, laughter)</font>

03:10.738 --> 03:12.775
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

03:16.712 --> 03:18.881
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADRID</b></font>:
My favorite thing,

03:18.914 --> 03:21.984
open 24 hours,
the candy station.

03:22.016 --> 03:24.287
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>:
Oh, my God. Come on, Trent.

03:27.688 --> 03:29.257
<font color="#87CEFA">(Maddox speaks indistinctly)</font>

03:29.290 --> 03:32.127
Mix the vanilla
and strawberry in it.

03:33.729 --> 03:35.698
Say hi, Trent.

03:35.730 --> 03:37.098
Hi.

03:37.131 --> 03:38.767
I'm Idlib.

03:38.801 --> 03:40.836
My uncle's
the resort manager here.

03:40.868 --> 03:43.171
He's Trent. I'm Maddox.

03:43.205 --> 03:45.040
I can do a 1,000-piece
jigsaw puzzle,

03:45.073 --> 03:46.708
which is a considerable
thing to do.

03:46.742 --> 03:48.544
My dad and I put
clear glue on them

03:48.576 --> 03:50.178
and hang them on my wall.

03:50.212 --> 03:52.748
I collect conch shells.

03:52.781 --> 03:54.817
I have 42 conch shells.

03:55.818 --> 03:57.754
Amazing.

03:59.053 --> 04:01.089
- Okay.
- I might need a little help with this.

04:01.123 --> 04:02.892
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: Right, so you do
strawberry and vanilla?

04:06.093 --> 04:07.763
<font color="#87CEFA">(Maddox giggles)</font>

04:14.503 --> 04:15.938
Hi.

04:15.970 --> 04:17.204
Thank you.

04:17.238 --> 04:18.741
Yes. Ah, okay.

04:18.774 --> 04:20.142
Okay, I got it.

04:20.173 --> 04:21.442
Okay. Come on.

04:21.476 --> 04:22.811
Thank you.

04:22.844 --> 04:24.979
<font color="#87CEFA">(chuckles)</font> Great job helping.

04:25.012 --> 04:26.616
Yes.

04:29.250 --> 04:31.953
<font color="#87CEFA">(Trent yells playfully)</font>

04:31.986 --> 04:33.455
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
You!

04:33.488 --> 04:35.157
I touched your jacket.
That counts.

04:35.190 --> 04:36.659
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
Hey.

04:36.691 --> 04:38.993
There's 250,000
furniture-related injuries

04:39.027 --> 04:40.996
in the United States per year.

04:41.029 --> 04:44.834
25% of those...
coffee table injuries.

04:44.866 --> 04:47.068
Hey. Hey!

04:47.101 --> 04:49.003
- Fine.
- Okay.

04:49.037 --> 04:51.106
<font color="#87CEFA">(kids chattering playfully
in distance)</font>

04:52.508 --> 04:54.075
<font color="#87CEFA">(door opens)</font>

04:54.109 --> 04:55.478
<font color="#87CEFA">(door closes)</font>

04:58.012 --> 05:01.950
Warren and Warren must be
affiliated with this resort.

05:01.984 --> 05:04.053
They must have conventions here.

05:05.953 --> 05:09.257
We love this
pharmaceutical company at work.

05:09.291 --> 05:10.826
We're considering
asking our clients

05:10.859 --> 05:12.294
to use Warren and Warren drugs

05:12.327 --> 05:14.029
as a way to lower
their insurance rates.

05:14.061 --> 05:16.464
<font color="#87CEFA">(Maddox and Trent laughing)</font>

05:16.498 --> 05:18.367
Ah, hmm. Yeah.

05:19.500 --> 05:21.936
"No kids allowed on the beach"?

05:21.969 --> 05:23.938
What? Hold on.

05:23.972 --> 05:25.940
<font color="#87CEFA">(gasps)</font> "No Kids Week"?

05:25.974 --> 05:27.610
- That's not true!
- It says no ki...

05:27.642 --> 05:29.111
- Let me see that!
- Prisca, you should've checked.

05:29.144 --> 05:30.446
- Let me see that!
- It's your mom's fault.

05:30.479 --> 05:31.947
- Let me see!
- No, no, no, really.

05:31.979 --> 05:33.616
- No, it says this. No.
- Oh, my God, let me see.

05:33.649 --> 05:34.850
- She should've checked. It says this.
- Let me see!

05:34.883 --> 05:36.318
- Yes, of course.
- Let me see!

05:36.351 --> 05:37.887
<font color="#87CEFA">(laughing)</font> I know this is
very painful news

05:37.919 --> 05:39.888
- for you all to bear, but now...
- Let me see!

05:39.921 --> 05:41.890
- ...now I've gotten power.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: No!

05:41.924 --> 05:43.625
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
Yes. And you have to do it.

05:43.659 --> 05:45.127
Yes, you have to understand.

05:45.159 --> 05:47.029
It's like this.
Life is like this.

05:47.061 --> 05:50.164
It's tough, and sometimes things
don't go the way you want.

05:50.198 --> 05:52.868
("Kirahu E" by Mila playing)

05:54.036 --> 05:56.071
WOMAN: <font color="#87CEFA">(laughing)</font>
Oh, my gosh.

05:56.104 --> 05:58.508
<font color="#87CEFA">(indistinct conversations)</font>

06:03.277 --> 06:06.381
Come on. Blue team's winning.

06:06.414 --> 06:08.183
<font color="#8B814C"><b>BOY</b></font>:
Ah, good hit.

06:09.116 --> 06:11.253
What's your name, and what
do you do for a living?

06:11.286 --> 06:12.488
Hey, guys. I'm Annette.

06:12.520 --> 06:14.088
And what's your name?

06:14.121 --> 06:15.356
I'm Trent. This is Idlib.

06:15.390 --> 06:17.325
Hey, nice to meet you.

06:17.359 --> 06:18.693
- Bye.
- Bye.

06:18.726 --> 06:20.296
Bye.

06:23.130 --> 06:25.200
Hi. I'm Trent. This is Idlib.

06:25.233 --> 06:27.603
What are your names, and what
do you do for a living?

06:27.635 --> 06:29.505
Oh, well, I'm Sophia Watson.

06:29.537 --> 06:30.738
I'm a chef.

06:30.772 --> 06:32.408
I'm Greg Mitchell. I'm a cop.

06:32.440 --> 06:33.676
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT and IDLIB</b></font>:
Cool.

06:33.709 --> 06:34.944
And I'm Malin Mitchell.

06:34.976 --> 06:36.412
I'm a dancer.

06:36.445 --> 06:37.746
Wow. That's cool.

06:37.779 --> 06:39.615
- Okay, bye.
- Bye.

06:39.647 --> 06:41.116
- Bye.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>IDLIB</b></font>: Bye.

06:41.149 --> 06:42.585
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: Hey, let's go over there.
- <font color="#87CEFA">(chuckling)</font>

06:42.618 --> 06:44.253
<font color="#87CEFA">(hip-hop playing)</font>

06:44.286 --> 06:46.822
<font color="#87CEFA">(indistinct chatter, laughter)</font>

06:56.097 --> 06:58.467
Truth-telling game. Go.

06:59.467 --> 07:01.303
I can't do a push-up. Go.

07:03.738 --> 07:05.775
I don't have friends.

07:06.775 --> 07:08.243
I'm your friend.

07:08.275 --> 07:09.711
You'll leave.

07:09.745 --> 07:11.547
My mom might let me
FaceTime you.

07:11.580 --> 07:13.382
Then we can be friends.

07:13.414 --> 07:16.284
You can come over to my house
and make up stories.

07:16.318 --> 07:18.988
Then we can go
to the same college together

07:19.020 --> 07:21.456
and become neighbors
with mortgages.

07:21.489 --> 07:23.825
<font color="#87CEFA">(chuckles)</font> Cool.

07:25.260 --> 07:26.428
<font color="#87CEFA">(water running)</font>

07:26.460 --> 07:27.830
<font color="#87CEFA">(faucet squeaks, water stops)</font>

07:27.863 --> 07:29.532
It's weird.

07:30.698 --> 07:32.800
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
I know.

07:32.834 --> 07:35.771
It's hanging over me.
I can barely eat.

07:35.803 --> 07:38.006
And I don't feel anything?

07:40.207 --> 07:42.243
We agreed... we'd give them

07:42.277 --> 07:44.647
one last vacation
before telling them.

07:44.679 --> 07:46.114
I can't understand why

07:46.147 --> 07:47.849
we don't take
into consideration...

07:47.883 --> 07:49.952
That shouldn't affect anything.

07:51.019 --> 07:53.989
The doctor said
it's a nonfactor.

07:54.022 --> 07:56.392
It's probably been there
for years, he said.

07:59.294 --> 08:02.330
We were on a course to separate.

08:02.363 --> 08:04.967
That's confusing enough for us.

08:05.000 --> 08:08.571
Let's not bring an irrelevant
medical condition into this.

08:10.072 --> 08:12.708
Let's get through this, Guy.

08:12.741 --> 08:14.842
Compartmentalize.

08:14.875 --> 08:16.678
It's only for three days.

08:16.712 --> 08:18.012
You found a place?

08:18.046 --> 08:19.647
Yes.

08:19.681 --> 08:21.817
Oh, Prisca, come on.

08:26.020 --> 08:29.123
You're always thinking
about the future!

08:29.157 --> 08:31.894
It makes me feel not seen!

08:31.926 --> 08:34.029
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: You're always thinking
about the past.

08:34.062 --> 08:36.399
You work in a goddamn museum!

08:41.202 --> 08:43.172
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>:
I think they stopped.

08:45.039 --> 08:46.708
Why don't you play?

09:00.956 --> 09:03.025
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

09:24.411 --> 09:26.448
<font color="#87CEFA">(laughing)</font>

09:27.716 --> 09:30.419
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

09:30.452 --> 09:32.487
<font color="#87CEFA">(birds calling)</font>

09:35.490 --> 09:38.260
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

09:59.114 --> 10:01.150
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

10:06.520 --> 10:07.923
<font color="#8B814C"><b>WAITER</b></font>:
Good morning.

10:07.956 --> 10:09.825
What would you like
for breakfast?

10:09.857 --> 10:11.827
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHRYSTAL</b></font>: I'll have
the Calcium Bomb juice drink.

10:11.860 --> 10:14.229
I have a calcium deficiency.

10:14.261 --> 10:16.731
So, is it really calcium-rich
or just a catchy name?

10:16.765 --> 10:20.669
<font color="#87CEFA">(chuckles)</font> It has all
calcium-rich vegetables, ma'am.

10:20.702 --> 10:22.070
Sit up, Kara, honey.

10:22.102 --> 10:23.771
- Okay.
- All right?

10:23.804 --> 10:25.606
You don't want to be hunched
when you grow up, baby.

10:25.640 --> 10:27.509
It's very unattractive.

10:27.542 --> 10:30.112
Boys will get turned off.

10:30.145 --> 10:32.380
Give me the Calcium Bomb juice.

10:33.615 --> 10:37.486
And maybe you could
recommend one of these.

10:40.621 --> 10:42.123
This one.

10:42.156 --> 10:44.726
<font color="#8B814C"><b>WAITER</b></font>: I recommend
the granola parfait.

10:46.494 --> 10:48.263
Um, it's a good choice.

10:48.295 --> 10:49.463
Okay.

10:49.496 --> 10:51.466
So, how is the Capa family?

10:51.499 --> 10:53.534
Any plans today?

10:53.568 --> 10:56.438
Well, one of our kids
wants to do Jet Ski,

10:56.471 --> 10:58.774
- and the other one...
- Mm-hmm.

10:58.807 --> 11:00.342
...wants to do
anything but that.

11:00.375 --> 11:02.177
<font color="#87CEFA">(chuckles)</font>

11:02.209 --> 11:05.479
Well, there's, um...
there's a private beach

11:05.513 --> 11:07.716
on the nature preserve side
of the island.

11:07.749 --> 11:09.151
It's impossible to find.

11:09.183 --> 11:10.952
It's surrounded
by stunning rocks,

11:10.986 --> 11:12.855
- very unusual minerals.
- Oh.

11:12.888 --> 11:15.557
Oh, it's a once-in-a-lifetime
experience, so...

11:15.590 --> 11:17.560
A natural anomaly.

11:18.994 --> 11:21.396
I only recommend it
to certain guests.

11:21.428 --> 11:23.497
But I liked you guys
immediately.

11:23.530 --> 11:25.066
All right? You're a nice family.

11:25.100 --> 11:28.303
So I-I could arrange
a van to take you, if...

11:28.336 --> 11:30.505
Hmm. Yeah.

11:30.538 --> 11:32.808
Sounds like
a great memory for us.

11:32.841 --> 11:34.209
It's our little secret.

11:34.241 --> 11:36.077
I'll make all the arrangements.

11:38.045 --> 11:40.549
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: Thank you.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: Thanks.

11:42.516 --> 11:43.885
Okay, so I think we should get

11:43.919 --> 11:45.687
the Calloway Kale-away
for Trent.

11:45.720 --> 11:47.222
Idlib, what did I tell you

11:47.255 --> 11:49.258
about being in here
when you shouldn't?

11:50.292 --> 11:52.861
You can't... You know,
I told you so many times.

11:52.894 --> 11:54.496
You know, we have certain...

11:54.529 --> 11:57.399
- <font color="#87CEFA">(glass shattering)</font>
- <font color="#87CEFA">(people murmuring, gasping)</font>

12:04.706 --> 12:06.241
I'm a doctor.

12:06.274 --> 12:07.775
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>:
My wife has epilepsy.

12:07.808 --> 12:08.876
I'm a nurse.

12:08.909 --> 12:09.978
My name is Jarin.

12:10.978 --> 12:12.680
Right, she's having
a grand mal seizure.

12:12.713 --> 12:14.916
Keep things away
from her, please.

12:14.949 --> 12:16.985
<font color="#87CEFA">(gasping, coughing)</font>

12:18.218 --> 12:19.921
Patricia?

12:19.954 --> 12:21.522
Doll?

12:21.555 --> 12:23.257
All right, Jack,
I think if you just leave her

12:23.290 --> 12:24.525
lying here for a while,
put something under her head,

12:24.558 --> 12:25.593
I think she'll be fine.

12:25.626 --> 12:26.895
Thank you, Doctor.

12:26.928 --> 12:28.230
It's Jarin, by the way.

12:31.399 --> 12:34.702
For my next act,
I'll spin my head around 360.

12:34.736 --> 12:36.972
<font color="#87CEFA">(laughs)</font>

12:37.005 --> 12:39.573
I'm sorry I ruined
everyone's breakfast.

12:39.606 --> 12:41.543
You always want to be
the center of attention.

12:41.576 --> 12:43.545
<font color="#87CEFA">(Patricia laughs)</font>

12:43.577 --> 12:44.980
My goodness.

12:45.013 --> 12:46.648
Let's get you
something to drink?

12:46.680 --> 12:48.382
<font color="#87CEFA">(sighs)</font>
Yeah.

12:48.415 --> 12:49.818
<font color="#87CEFA">(cell phone buttons
clicking rapidly)</font>

12:49.851 --> 12:53.288
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  I'll wash away someday  ♫</i> </font>

12:53.321 --> 12:56.558
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  No monuments made in my name  ♫</i> </font>

12:56.591 --> 12:58.827
- Idlib?
- <font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  There is no life  ♫</i> </font>

12:58.860 --> 13:00.462
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  I'd trade  ♫</i> </font>

13:00.495 --> 13:02.998
- <font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  You are my reason  ♫</i> </font>
- <font color="#87CEFA">(door opens)</font>

13:03.030 --> 13:05.500
- <font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  To remain...  ♫</i> </font>
- <font color="#87CEFA">(door closes)</font>

13:06.500 --> 13:08.536
<font color="#87CEFA">(engine starts)</font>

13:11.271 --> 13:13.275
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>: Oh, can't be
that secret of a beach.

13:13.308 --> 13:14.809
We were told to keep it quiet.

13:14.842 --> 13:16.510
- So were we.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>AGNES</b></font>: Sit down, Gustav.

13:16.544 --> 13:19.347
Good boy.

13:19.380 --> 13:21.850
- Come. Stay.
- <font color="#87CEFA">(dog barks)</font>

13:21.882 --> 13:24.285
<font color="#87CEFA">(doors close)</font>

13:24.318 --> 13:26.188
<font color="#8B814C"><b>DRIVER</b></font>:
Okay, guest checklist.

13:26.221 --> 13:28.123
Books, sunscreen.

13:28.155 --> 13:30.825
Did everybody leave
their passports in their safes?

13:30.858 --> 13:32.526
I don't want anybody
to lose anything.

13:32.559 --> 13:33.828
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA and GUY</b></font>:
Yeah.

13:33.861 --> 13:36.497
What are your names
and occupations?

13:39.867 --> 13:42.470
<font color="#87CEFA">(birds chirping)</font>

13:42.504 --> 13:44.539
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

13:46.707 --> 13:48.743
<font color="#87CEFA">(gate rattling)</font>

