<font color="#8B814C"><b>DRIVER</b></font>:
Okay, my friends.

14:11.698 --> 14:13.734
You can just call us,
and we'll pick you up

14:13.768 --> 14:15.637
whenever you're ready
to come back.

14:15.669 --> 14:17.572
Or I'll pick you up at 5:00 p.m.

14:17.605 --> 14:19.975
Just follow the path
down to the beach.

14:20.007 --> 14:22.543
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: Is that also food?
- Yeah.

14:22.577 --> 14:25.547
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
Wow. That's a lot of food.

14:25.579 --> 14:27.515
Well, kids eat a lot of food.

14:27.549 --> 14:29.217
And you got
three of them with you.

14:29.250 --> 14:31.086
Okay. <font color="#87CEFA">(grunts)</font>

14:31.119 --> 14:33.789
Seems like a waste,
but thank you.

14:37.125 --> 14:39.394
Could you help us carry
some of these bags, please?

14:39.427 --> 14:41.663
We've got an elderly person
here and a child.

14:41.696 --> 14:43.565
<font color="#8B814C"><b>DRIVER</b></font>:
I'm sorry. I got to get back.

14:43.597 --> 14:45.400
But it's not far.
Just walk down.

14:45.433 --> 14:47.169
You'll see a beautiful
slot canyon.

14:47.202 --> 14:49.004
Walk through that, and in
a few minutes, you'll be there.

14:49.036 --> 14:50.404
Enjoy, everybody.

14:50.438 --> 14:52.274
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: Do you think there's...
- Come on.

14:52.307 --> 14:54.443
Do you think there's snakes?

14:54.476 --> 14:55.610
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>:
Of course.

14:55.643 --> 14:56.778
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
Cool. I want to see one.

14:56.810 --> 14:58.779
- <font color="#87CEFA">(van departs)</font>
- <font color="#87CEFA">(birds calling)</font>

14:58.813 --> 15:02.484
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: Gorgeous.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: Wow. <font color="#87CEFA">(laughs)</font>

15:04.751 --> 15:06.421
<font color="#8B814C"><b>AGNES</b></font>:
Okay.

15:08.655 --> 15:10.424
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
You okay?

15:10.457 --> 15:12.493
Yeah?

15:17.499 --> 15:19.568
<font color="#87CEFA">(quiet, indistinct chatter)</font>

15:21.401 --> 15:23.371
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

15:23.404 --> 15:25.974
<font color="#87CEFA">(laughter)</font>

15:26.006 --> 15:28.910
- <font color="#87CEFA">(birds squawking)</font>
- <font color="#87CEFA">(Maddox screams, laughs)</font>

15:31.178 --> 15:32.948
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: Could, uh,
someone please tell me

15:32.981 --> 15:34.316
- what just happened?
- <font color="#87CEFA">(laughter)</font>

15:34.348 --> 15:35.583
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>:
Look out.

15:35.616 --> 15:36.985
<font color="#8B814C"><b>AGNES</b></font>:
Oh, this is so exciting.

15:37.018 --> 15:38.386
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
Careful, Maddox.

15:38.419 --> 15:40.456
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

15:47.028 --> 15:48.663
<font color="#87CEFA">(Maddox and Trent laughing)</font>

15:48.696 --> 15:50.799
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: Let's go!
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: I'm gonna win.

15:50.832 --> 15:52.500
<font color="#87CEFA">(Maddox whoops)</font>

15:52.534 --> 15:54.803
<font color="#87CEFA">(kids' laughter continues)</font>

16:02.843 --> 16:04.879
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

16:18.525 --> 16:19.827
Wow.

16:19.861 --> 16:21.462
I just got chills.

16:23.198 --> 16:24.933
- <font color="#87CEFA">(grunts)</font>
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>AGNES</b></font>: Come on, darling.

16:24.966 --> 16:27.302
Let's show Gustav the sea.

16:29.169 --> 16:31.106
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
Hey. Maddox, Maddox, look.

16:31.139 --> 16:32.941
Listen, I...
Let's move somewhere else.

16:32.973 --> 16:34.975
I think it's much nicer
closer to the water, right?

16:35.009 --> 16:36.611
- No, but I...
- No, it's...

16:36.644 --> 16:38.413
Look, it's beautiful.

16:51.992 --> 16:54.195
<font color="#8B814C"><b>AGNES</b></font>: Have you ever seen
anything like that?

16:54.228 --> 16:56.297
<font color="#87CEFA">(Agnes whoops)</font>

16:56.331 --> 16:58.400
- <font color="#87CEFA">(camera clicking)</font>
- <font color="#87CEFA">(Gustav barks)</font>

16:58.433 --> 17:01.303
<font color="#8B814C"><b>AGNES</b></font>:
They were right to send us.

17:01.336 --> 17:03.505
- <font color="#87CEFA">(barking)</font>
- Lie down.

17:03.538 --> 17:05.306
<font color="#87CEFA">(rattling)</font>

17:05.339 --> 17:07.242
Good boy.

17:07.275 --> 17:08.742
<font color="#87CEFA">(playful chatter)</font>

17:08.775 --> 17:11.178
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: Kids, look at
the beautiful coral.

17:11.211 --> 17:13.414
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
I'm gonna get... Aah! Stop!

17:13.448 --> 17:14.915
What are you going to do?

17:14.948 --> 17:16.517
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
Now I'm gonna splash you.

17:16.550 --> 17:18.419
Just keep on reading, I guess.

17:18.453 --> 17:20.355
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
You just splashed me.

17:20.387 --> 17:21.856
Stop!

17:21.888 --> 17:23.992
- I didn't mean to splash you.
- <font color="#87CEFA">(Maddox laughs)</font>

17:24.025 --> 17:26.294
- Guy?
- Yeah.

17:27.428 --> 17:29.264
What book am I reading?

17:29.296 --> 17:31.365
<font color="#87CEFA">(Trent and Maddox laughing)</font>

17:34.101 --> 17:35.970
I don't know.

17:36.970 --> 17:38.739
Why?

17:39.740 --> 17:41.409
No reason.

17:45.380 --> 17:49.284
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: Prisca, I wanted
to tell you something.

17:53.655 --> 17:55.590
No, never mind.

17:55.622 --> 17:57.391
I'll tell you later.

18:02.596 --> 18:04.698
Oh, my God.

18:04.732 --> 18:06.935
That's Mid-Sized Sedan.

18:06.967 --> 18:08.637
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
What? Mid what?

18:08.669 --> 18:10.138
He's a rapper.

18:10.170 --> 18:12.806
"More Dough for the Cookin'"?

18:12.840 --> 18:14.442
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: Mid-Sized Sedan?
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: Begin an activity.

18:14.475 --> 18:15.877
- Dad, I have to. I have to!
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>: Yes. Okay.

18:15.909 --> 18:17.211
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
You and Mom on one side.

18:17.245 --> 18:18.446
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
No, no, no, no, no. Leave him.

18:18.478 --> 18:20.047
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
Sounds like fun. Come on.

18:20.081 --> 18:21.082
No, because it's, like,
a private, you know...

18:21.114 --> 18:22.284
No, Dad, stop! I need to say hi.

18:22.316 --> 18:23.418
He's on vacation.
He's on vacation.

18:23.450 --> 18:24.486
What's his surname? Sedan?

18:24.518 --> 18:26.988
<font color="#87CEFA">(whooping, laughing)</font>

18:28.288 --> 18:30.624
Oh! Oh.

18:30.658 --> 18:32.394
Whoa. <font color="#87CEFA">(grunts)</font>

18:32.427 --> 18:33.461
Whoa. All right.

18:33.494 --> 18:35.496
Here's a big one. Aah!

18:35.530 --> 18:37.432
<font color="#8B814C"><b>KARA</b></font>:
Help me with this.

18:38.800 --> 18:41.536
We should have
a housewarming party.

18:42.704 --> 18:45.374
Isn't our house so beautiful?

18:46.341 --> 18:48.109
<font color="#87CEFA">(water trickling)</font>

18:48.141 --> 18:50.178
<font color="#87CEFA">(waves sloshing)</font>

18:58.553 --> 19:00.188
- Boo!
- Aah! You!

19:00.220 --> 19:02.089
- Come. Come back here!
- No!

19:02.122 --> 19:03.591
<font color="#87CEFA">(Maddox and Kara laughing)</font>

19:03.623 --> 19:05.293
<font color="#8B814C"><b>KARA</b></font>:
Not gonna get me!

19:05.325 --> 19:07.328
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: Kara, you know,
I'm gonna get you right now.

19:07.361 --> 19:08.929
Come on.

19:08.963 --> 19:11.766
- Not gonna get me!
- No, I am.

19:11.798 --> 19:13.567
Come on, Kara.

19:14.968 --> 19:16.638
Whoa! Oh, my God.

19:16.670 --> 19:18.506
Caught you.

19:21.175 --> 19:23.278
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
Ha. Never gonna catch me.

19:23.311 --> 19:25.447
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

19:25.479 --> 19:27.614
<font color="#8B814C"><b>KARA</b></font>:
Honey, I'm home.

19:27.648 --> 19:30.217
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: I told you,
I don't want to live like this.

19:30.251 --> 19:32.320
I'm gonna live in a condominium.

19:32.352 --> 19:34.689
I'm going for a drive
to calm down.

19:35.689 --> 19:38.192
I'm really, really hungry.

19:38.226 --> 19:40.895
Me, too. My stomach's growling.

19:40.928 --> 19:42.597
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>:
Me, too.

19:57.378 --> 19:59.813
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>:
Wow.

19:59.846 --> 20:01.882
Who would leave this?

20:02.949 --> 20:04.919
Hey, Mom!

20:04.951 --> 20:06.854
From the hotel!

20:06.888 --> 20:08.523
They're so rusted.

20:08.555 --> 20:10.158
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
Put that down!

20:10.190 --> 20:13.594
You can get infected
or you'll cut yourself.

20:13.628 --> 20:15.362
Come away.

20:15.396 --> 20:17.098
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: Next activity.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: What's happening?

20:17.130 --> 20:18.666
- Let's play hide-and-seek.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>: I don't know.

20:18.698 --> 20:20.869
They found stuff
from the hotel in the sand.

20:22.870 --> 20:26.006
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>:
18, 19, 20.

20:26.040 --> 20:28.510
- No fish.
- Ready or not, here we come!

20:28.543 --> 20:30.245
<font color="#87CEFA">(laughing)</font>

20:31.746 --> 20:33.415
<font color="#87CEFA">(chuckling)</font>

20:35.983 --> 20:38.053
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

20:45.258 --> 20:46.727
Mom!

20:47.894 --> 20:49.963
Mom! Mom!

20:49.996 --> 20:53.634
Mom! Mom! Mom!

20:56.303 --> 20:58.238
What is it? What is it?

20:58.272 --> 20:59.908
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: Trent?
- Someone over there.

20:59.940 --> 21:01.275
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
Over where?

21:11.852 --> 21:14.422
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>: Come on,
give me a hand. Get the legs.

21:24.031 --> 21:25.233
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
Make your list.

21:25.265 --> 21:26.734
- Make your list.
- Okay.

21:26.766 --> 21:28.268
- Red and orange.
- Red, orange.

21:28.302 --> 21:30.103
Come away from here, babies.

21:30.137 --> 21:32.841
Let the doctor try
and help this lady, yeah?

21:32.873 --> 21:34.708
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: Green.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>: Green.

21:36.878 --> 21:38.079
- Tan.
- Tan.

21:38.111 --> 21:39.313
- Purple.
- Purple.

21:39.346 --> 21:40.814
- What happened?
- It's okay.

21:40.848 --> 21:42.650
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: Blue.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>: Blue. Blue is good.

21:42.682 --> 21:44.151
- In there.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: Green.

21:44.185 --> 21:45.419
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>: Green, yes.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: Yellow.

21:45.453 --> 21:46.754
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
Yellow. I love yellow.

21:46.786 --> 21:48.689
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
Call the police, right?

21:48.723 --> 21:51.192
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>:
I'll get my mobile.

21:51.225 --> 21:53.194
Oh, damn.

21:53.226 --> 21:55.296
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

22:13.080 --> 22:14.849
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>:
What happened to her, Mom?

22:14.881 --> 22:16.551
I don't know.

22:17.552 --> 22:19.920
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: I'm still hungry.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>KARA</b></font>: Me, too.

22:21.988 --> 22:23.357
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
Was she with you?

22:23.390 --> 22:25.325
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MID-SIZED SEDAN</b></font>:
I was waiting for her.

22:25.359 --> 22:27.328
She swam out by herself.

22:27.361 --> 22:30.899
Yo, I don't know
what the hell happened.

22:30.931 --> 22:33.400
I ain't saying nothing else.

22:33.434 --> 22:34.836
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>:
Did you strike him?

22:34.869 --> 22:36.471
I don't need to know
the context of...

22:36.504 --> 22:38.305
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
What? No. Of course not.

22:38.339 --> 22:40.909
So why's your nose bleeding?

22:40.941 --> 22:43.844
I told y'all, I ain't got
nothing to say to you.

22:47.247 --> 22:49.284
My chest feels funny.

22:50.851 --> 22:52.687
- Well, you know,
- <font color="#87CEFA">(sighs)</font>

22:52.719 --> 22:55.422
we should've gotten a yacht,
like I suggested, Agnes.

22:55.456 --> 22:58.426
You shouldn't have
fought me on that.

22:58.458 --> 23:01.328
You see? Now we're mixed up
in some island issue.

23:01.361 --> 23:03.398
I mean, I... <font color="#87CEFA">(scoffs)</font>

23:05.765 --> 23:08.268
<font color="#87CEFA">(Agnes wheezes softly)</font>

23:08.302 --> 23:11.039
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
Mom, my swimsuit is hurting.

23:11.072 --> 23:12.607
I have to take it off.

23:12.640 --> 23:14.809
Well, just loosen your...

23:19.813 --> 23:21.949
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
We're from Philadelphia.

23:21.983 --> 23:24.284
I'm on a break here with
my wife and kids. That's them.

23:24.317 --> 23:26.987
That... Well, yeah, over there.

23:28.989 --> 23:32.226
And for the record, I know
most people who die on vacation

23:32.258 --> 23:35.896
die from sun exposure,
overexertion,

23:35.929 --> 23:38.565
overindulgence
of food or alcohol

23:38.599 --> 23:41.769
or-or a mixture of all
of the above 99.4% of the time.

23:41.802 --> 23:43.771
- How you know all this?
- I'm an actuary.

23:43.803 --> 23:45.773
I calculate people's
insurance rates

23:45.805 --> 23:47.842
based on their risk profile.

23:49.310 --> 23:51.580
I ain't do nothing, man.

23:54.148 --> 23:56.016
She was into me.

23:58.619 --> 24:01.422
Somebody will figure this out.

24:01.455 --> 24:03.890
We'll just have to wait
for them to get here.

24:03.923 --> 24:06.960
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>:
No reception at all.

24:06.994 --> 24:09.496
I guess our beach day's over.

24:09.530 --> 24:11.833
You got to keep an eye
on him and the body.

24:11.865 --> 24:14.301
<font color="#87CEFA">(laughs, whoops)</font>

24:15.936 --> 24:18.406
Oh, my goodness.

24:18.438 --> 24:20.207
Wow.

24:22.376 --> 24:24.812
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>: Did you just get
dropped off by the resort?

24:24.844 --> 24:26.346
Yeah. We were supposed
to come earlier,

24:26.380 --> 24:28.282
but we rested in the room first.

24:28.314 --> 24:29.917
Great. We have to get
the resort people

24:29.949 --> 24:31.419
before they leave.

24:31.451 --> 24:33.121
I think we will all
have to leave this beach.

24:33.153 --> 24:34.354
Wait. Why?

24:34.388 --> 24:35.657
They left already.

24:35.689 --> 24:37.057
What happened?

24:49.402 --> 24:50.971
We really don't know
what happened.

24:51.005 --> 24:53.107
Well, I think this man had
something to do with it.

24:53.140 --> 24:54.475
Man, if I was involved,

24:54.507 --> 24:55.876
why would I be
standing around, bro?

24:55.909 --> 24:57.711
- Damn.
- His nose is bleeding.

24:57.745 --> 24:59.280
I think he got that when she
was trying to defend herself.

24:59.313 --> 25:01.049
I don't like
this dynamic at all.

25:01.082 --> 25:03.051
Yo, my nose has been bleeding
for hours, man.

25:03.083 --> 25:05.053
I don't know why
it's doing that.

25:05.085 --> 25:06.688
Charles, something's wrong
with your mother.

25:06.720 --> 25:08.756
She's asking for you, honey.

25:10.357 --> 25:12.560
Well, we're all in this now.

25:12.592 --> 25:14.728
We are responsible
for that woman.

25:14.762 --> 25:16.397
And I've got nothing
against this man.

25:16.429 --> 25:19.366
I'm just doing
what needs to be done.

25:19.400 --> 25:21.703
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>: No cell phone reception
on this beach.

25:21.736 --> 25:23.137
You stay here.

25:23.169 --> 25:24.471
I'll go to the clearing
in the jungle

25:24.505 --> 25:25.907
where they dropped us
and try to call.

25:25.939 --> 25:27.808
They obviously have
a signal out here.

25:27.842 --> 25:30.344
- How else do people call to go back?
- Right.

25:40.888 --> 25:43.425
<font color="#87CEFA">(groaning, gasping)</font>

25:47.695 --> 25:50.164
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PATRICIA</b></font>:
Oh, my God.

25:50.197 --> 25:52.366
You stumbled back out.
You were holding your head.

25:52.399 --> 25:55.268
You looked like
you were in pain, babe.

25:55.302 --> 25:57.938
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: You blacked out.
- <font color="#87CEFA">(scoffs)</font>

25:57.971 --> 26:00.040
I felt this pressure in my head.

26:01.475 --> 26:03.311
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PATRICIA</b></font>:
Are you okay?

26:04.711 --> 26:06.279
<font color="#8B814C"><b>AGNES</b></font>:
I'm fine, Charles.

26:06.313 --> 26:08.448
I-I think it's the shock.

26:08.482 --> 26:09.884
<font color="#87CEFA">(Gustav barking)</font>

26:09.917 --> 26:11.886
Try to help Gustav,
or he'll be sick.

26:11.919 --> 26:13.720
Yeah, of course it's the shock.

26:13.754 --> 26:15.723
Listen, I'm gonna get a van
to take us back to the resort,

26:15.755 --> 26:18.092
but first, I've got to deal
with all this, all right?

26:18.124 --> 26:19.726
Are you okay?

26:19.759 --> 26:21.361
Yeah.

26:21.394 --> 26:23.630
I know you've been stressed.

26:23.663 --> 26:26.233
Don't let this upset you.

26:26.266 --> 26:28.702
Help these people
through this, Charles.

26:28.736 --> 26:30.271
<font color="#87CEFA">(Gustav barking)</font>

26:30.303 --> 26:32.073
So, what did you hear?

26:33.640 --> 26:35.942
Help these people through
this, Charles. <font color="#87CEFA">(gasps)</font>

26:35.976 --> 26:37.845
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
Excuse me.

26:39.746 --> 26:42.717
Excuse me. I saw you were
talking to my husband.

26:42.749 --> 26:45.419
I know you're dealing with a
lot with that woman right now,

26:45.451 --> 26:47.420
but something is wrong
with my son.

26:47.454 --> 26:49.323
- Some kind of reaction.
- Is... is it severe?

26:49.355 --> 26:51.057
I don't have time for this.

26:51.091 --> 26:52.894
- What kind of doctor are you?
- <font color="#87CEFA">(Gustav barks)</font>

26:52.927 --> 26:55.329
I'm a cardiothoracic surgeon
and chief medical officer.

26:55.361 --> 26:57.631
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
You don't know me.

26:57.665 --> 27:00.635
- I curate exhibits for museums.
- <font color="#87CEFA">(whimpers, barks)</font>

27:00.668 --> 27:02.837
I'm telling you this
because I want you to trust me

27:02.870 --> 27:04.839
and not think I'm being
hysterical when I say

27:04.871 --> 27:07.475
there's something very wrong
with my child.

27:07.507 --> 27:09.777
He seems fine to me.
He's playing with my daughter.

27:10.878 --> 27:12.947
TRENT: <font color="#87CEFA">(older voice)</font>
You look different, too.

27:12.979 --> 27:14.681
MADDOX: <font color="#87CEFA">(older voice)</font>
How?

27:14.715 --> 27:16.516
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
Uh, I don't know.

27:16.550 --> 27:18.453
You just look different.

27:19.519 --> 27:21.354
KARA: <font color="#87CEFA">(older voice)</font>
Hold my hand.

27:21.388 --> 27:23.323
Okay.

27:25.626 --> 27:27.094
Willow.

27:27.127 --> 27:30.031
Japanese maple. Evergreen.

27:30.063 --> 27:32.300
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: If you get scared,
just tell me, okay?

27:33.667 --> 27:35.703
What do you keep looking at?

27:35.736 --> 27:37.805
- There.
- Where?

27:39.038 --> 27:42.108
Way, way up there
on the side of the hillside.

27:42.141 --> 27:43.710
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>:
What do you see?

27:43.744 --> 27:46.280
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: I thought I saw
something shiny.

27:46.313 --> 27:47.748
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>:
Here comes Mom.

27:51.185 --> 27:54.722
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHRYSTAL</b></font>:
Charles, she stopped breathing!

27:54.755 --> 27:56.824
She stopped breathing!

27:58.691 --> 28:00.894
I didn't do anything, Charles.

28:00.928 --> 28:03.030
You guys just...
you just walked away,

28:03.063 --> 28:05.399
and she just stopped breathing
all of a sudden.

28:05.431 --> 28:07.067
She... I mean, she was peaceful.

28:07.101 --> 28:09.337
Can you step back, please?

28:09.370 --> 28:11.539
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>: We'll take the kids
away from here.

28:11.572 --> 28:13.541
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHRYSTAL</b></font>:
Is this happening?

28:13.573 --> 28:15.909
<font color="#87CEFA">(Gustav barking)</font>

28:20.514 --> 28:22.550
<font color="#87CEFA">(Charles sobs)</font>

28:25.552 --> 28:28.589
- She couldn't take the shock.
- <font color="#87CEFA">(Chrystal crying)</font>

28:28.621 --> 28:32.060
She-she saw a murdered woman,
and her heart couldn't take it.

28:33.127 --> 28:35.563
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: What are your names
and occupations?

28:35.595 --> 28:37.931
I'm Jarin. I'm a nurse.

28:37.965 --> 28:40.501
I'm Patricia.
I'm a psychologist.

28:40.534 --> 28:42.402
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>:
He remembers everyone's names

28:42.436 --> 28:44.772
and things about them.

28:44.804 --> 28:46.908
Everything's gonna be okay.

28:46.940 --> 28:48.575
What's your name?

28:48.609 --> 28:50.177
I'm Trent.

28:50.209 --> 28:51.845
This is my sister Maddox.

28:51.879 --> 28:53.514
How old are you guys?

28:53.546 --> 28:56.516
- I'll guess. I'm good at this.
- <font color="#87CEFA">(chuckles)</font>

28:56.550 --> 28:58.719
You're 11, right, Trent?

28:58.752 --> 29:00.922
<font color="#87CEFA">(chuckling)</font>
I'm six.

29:00.955 --> 29:02.456
No.

29:02.488 --> 29:04.525
Really, are you ten, 11?

29:04.557 --> 29:07.260
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>:
He's not lying. He's six.

29:07.294 --> 29:10.531
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: I'm specifically
six and a quarter.

29:10.563 --> 29:12.800
She's 11.

29:12.832 --> 29:16.137
They're feeling unsafe.
There is a lot going on here.

29:16.169 --> 29:17.971
They're playing with us.

29:18.005 --> 29:19.607
Let's leave it.

29:19.640 --> 29:22.610
Okay, what's
your best friend's name?

29:22.642 --> 29:24.444
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
Maddox.

29:24.477 --> 29:26.313
How sweet.

29:26.346 --> 29:28.415
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
Have you seen my children?

29:28.448 --> 29:30.051
<font color="#87CEFA">(chuckles)</font>

29:30.083 --> 29:32.320
Is-is everyone trying
to play a joke on us?

29:32.352 --> 29:34.921
- What?
- Aren't these your children?

29:34.955 --> 29:36.991
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
I'm right here, Mom.

29:39.459 --> 29:41.261
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>:
Mom?

29:42.262 --> 29:43.831
Mom.

29:51.772 --> 29:54.042
Why are you looking
at me like that?

30:04.017 --> 30:06.586
Prisca.

30:06.620 --> 30:08.755
I think we should leave.

30:08.788 --> 30:10.757
Get the kids back to the resort.

30:10.791 --> 30:12.493
Guy.

30:29.509 --> 30:32.179
- Maddox?
- Yeah. Dad, it's me.

30:35.716 --> 30:37.584
What's going on?

30:48.594 --> 30:51.098
You see? You see?

30:54.368 --> 30:56.938
<font color="#87CEFA">(panting)</font>

31:08.082 --> 31:10.650
<font color="#87CEFA">(groaning)</font>

31:10.684 --> 31:12.853
<font color="#87CEFA">(trembling breaths)</font>

31:12.886 --> 31:14.922
<font color="#87CEFA">(panting)</font>

31:16.923 --> 31:18.558
<font color="#87CEFA">(whimpers)</font>

31:23.897 --> 31:26.700
<font color="#87CEFA">(grunts, groans)</font>

31:26.733 --> 31:28.602
<font color="#87CEFA">(panting)</font>

31:34.541 --> 31:35.976
<font color="#87CEFA">(grunts)</font>

31:38.579 --> 31:40.114
<font color="#87CEFA">(grunts)</font>

31:43.050 --> 31:45.351
Damn.

31:45.384 --> 31:48.588
- How'd we get here?
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>PATRICIA</b></font>: Take it easy.

31:48.621 --> 31:50.423
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>:
Intense cranial pressure.

31:50.457 --> 31:52.493
It's like being deep underwater.

31:54.328 --> 31:57.398
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PATRICIA</b></font>: Hey, can you get up?
Whoa, whoa, whoa, take it easy.

31:59.632 --> 32:01.134
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHRYSTAL</b></font>:
Charles?

32:01.168 --> 32:02.703
- Yeah, no, I'm-I'm all right.
- You okay?

32:02.736 --> 32:04.271
I'm fine. I'm all good.

32:04.303 --> 32:06.073
We're leaving right now,
and we're taking our kids.

32:06.105 --> 32:08.942
For some reason, people are
blacking out going this way.

32:08.976 --> 32:10.777
Three people
have blacked out now.

32:10.811 --> 32:12.246
- That's ridiculous. Come, move.
- No, no, no.

32:12.278 --> 32:14.114
I saw it, Prisca.
I saw Jarin black out.

32:14.148 --> 32:17.751
What I know is that we have to
get these kids to a hospital.

32:17.784 --> 32:19.620
Now.

32:19.652 --> 32:21.755
Look, let's stop
talking about it.

32:21.787 --> 32:23.591
The kids are scared.

32:23.623 --> 32:27.093
I can stay here with them,
but everyone else should try

32:27.127 --> 32:30.563
and find a different pathway
off this beach.

32:30.596 --> 32:32.565
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>:
Break off into groups of two

32:32.599 --> 32:34.601
in case people black out.

32:36.035 --> 32:38.005
Chrystal, go with me.

32:38.037 --> 32:40.107
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

32:51.185 --> 32:52.486
<font color="#87CEFA">(Chrystal gasps)</font>

32:52.518 --> 32:54.354
<font color="#87CEFA">(Charles groans)</font>

32:55.322 --> 32:56.423
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>:
Whoa.

32:56.456 --> 32:58.125
Whatever you do,
just stay close.

32:58.158 --> 33:00.494
- I'm feeling very uncomfortable right now.
- Just... Hmm?

33:00.526 --> 33:02.028
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>:
Don't get up too quickly.

33:02.062 --> 33:04.497
Kids, let Mom and Dad talk
for a second.

33:04.531 --> 33:07.334
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>:
No. Mom, we're scared.

33:07.367 --> 33:10.271
Please, stay right here.

33:10.303 --> 33:11.805
Okay?

33:12.805 --> 33:14.542
If I cry,
please don't let them see.

33:14.574 --> 33:15.842
I won't.

33:15.876 --> 33:17.011
Your hands are shaking.

33:17.044 --> 33:18.344
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

33:18.378 --> 33:20.414
- Yeah, they are.
- Yeah. You okay?

33:21.681 --> 33:24.217
We're on a beach
with two unrelated dead bodies.

33:24.251 --> 33:26.353
That is just
statistically impossible.

33:26.386 --> 33:28.289
All three kids are reacting
to something.

33:28.322 --> 33:29.857
Only the kids.

33:29.890 --> 33:32.059
I mean, look at
the doctor's daughter.

33:34.061 --> 33:36.330
The kids are reacting
to something they ate.

33:36.362 --> 33:38.698
Or they caught something.

33:38.732 --> 33:41.368
We're on a remote,
undeveloped island,

33:41.400 --> 33:44.404
but we have a doctor here, so...

33:44.438 --> 33:46.707
let's get the doc
to look at the kids.

33:54.680 --> 33:57.050
I still can't get any reception.

33:57.083 --> 33:59.719
Doctor, before we do
anything else,

33:59.753 --> 34:01.856
can you take a look
at our children, please?

34:03.023 --> 34:04.858
<font color="#87CEFA">(Mid-Sized Sedan yells in pain)</font>

34:04.890 --> 34:06.360
He's got a knife!

34:06.392 --> 34:07.861
<font color="#87CEFA">(groaning)</font>

34:07.893 --> 34:09.829
There's a damn hole in my cheek.

34:09.862 --> 34:11.431
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PATRICIA</b></font>:
Oh, my God. Are you okay?

34:11.465 --> 34:13.498
Put that down right now, Doctor.

34:13.532 --> 34:15.569
Watch out, Jarin.

34:16.570 --> 34:18.272
Listen, I don't know
why I did that.

34:18.304 --> 34:21.342
I thought he was
gonna hurt me. Sorry.

34:21.373 --> 34:22.775
Sorry.

34:22.809 --> 34:24.543
- What's he talking about, "sorry"?
- Okay.

34:24.577 --> 34:26.780
- Let me see that laceration.
- Man, that's assault, man!

34:26.813 --> 34:29.248
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>PATRICIA</b></font>: Just-just...
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>: Calm down.

34:29.282 --> 34:31.851
What's your name?

34:31.885 --> 34:33.754
Mid-Sized Sedan.

34:35.789 --> 34:37.424
I must be in shock. I'm numb.

34:37.456 --> 34:39.225
I'm not feeling
the pain no more.

34:39.257 --> 34:41.561
Please, let me see.

34:49.668 --> 34:51.371
No, this is not making
any sense, Prisca.

34:51.405 --> 34:53.572
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MID-SIZED SEDAN</b></font>: I need to get
my ass to a hospital now.

34:54.940 --> 34:57.178
What's with all y'all faces?

34:58.445 --> 35:01.082
It's hard to explain.

35:03.849 --> 35:05.985
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MID-SIZED SEDAN</b></font>:
This is messed-up, man.

35:06.019 --> 35:07.553
Where'd it go?

35:07.586 --> 35:09.555
This is some kind
of parlor trick.

35:09.588 --> 35:11.824
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MID-SIZED SEDAN</b></font>:
Yo, I know I tried to dip,

35:11.858 --> 35:14.262
but I am freaked, man.

35:15.262 --> 35:17.430
I just want to go back
to my hotel room.

35:17.463 --> 35:20.566
This was supposed to be
a zen trip, man.

35:20.599 --> 35:22.302
She and I only started talking

35:22.336 --> 35:24.104
because she was sick
and so am I.

35:24.137 --> 35:25.972
She had just been
diagnosed with MS,

35:26.006 --> 35:27.675
so we started rapping
about that.

35:27.707 --> 35:30.910
I didn't do nothing
to that girl, man.

35:30.943 --> 35:33.346
She was like Michael Phelps
swimming out there,

35:33.380 --> 35:34.814
backstroking and whatnot.

35:34.847 --> 35:36.449
She swam way the hell out.

35:36.483 --> 35:38.251
What did you say?

35:38.285 --> 35:40.020
No, I-I-I don't know, man.
Maybe it was butterfly stroke.

35:40.052 --> 35:41.587
I don't watch
the Summer Olympics like that.

35:41.621 --> 35:42.990
You came vacationing here
because you were sick,

35:43.023 --> 35:44.425
- and so did she?
- Yes.

35:44.457 --> 35:45.959
I thought that was
a cool coincidence.

35:45.992 --> 35:48.195
Maybe this is some kind
of group psychosis.

35:48.227 --> 35:49.829
I've studied this.

35:49.863 --> 35:52.599
We're all emotionally shaky
from our lives.

35:52.631 --> 35:56.003
We don't believe
we can leave this beach.

36:00.039 --> 36:02.442
<font color="#8B814C"><b>KARA</b></font>:
Mom, is there any more food?

36:02.476 --> 36:03.811
I'm still hungry.

36:03.843 --> 36:05.678
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>:
Well, she's definitely aged.

36:05.711 --> 36:07.680
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHRYSTAL</b></font>: Honey, how can you
still be hungry? We just...

36:07.713 --> 36:09.048
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>:
I'd put her biological age

36:09.081 --> 36:10.616
somewhere between 12 and 13,

36:10.650 --> 36:13.354
and she turned six
two weeks ago Tuesday.

36:13.387 --> 36:15.655
What?

36:15.689 --> 36:17.358
We're older?

36:18.557 --> 36:20.526
Am I okay?

36:20.559 --> 36:22.161
I don't know what's happening

36:22.195 --> 36:24.030
to the three of you, sweetheart.

36:24.064 --> 36:26.233
For now, I have
another swimsuit in my bag,

36:26.265 --> 36:29.635
and maybe you should
change into that.

36:29.668 --> 36:31.504
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>:
Uh, it might be a virus, maybe.

36:31.537 --> 36:33.240
Could be mosquitoes where...

36:33.273 --> 36:35.309
the way they behave
on this part of the island.

36:35.342 --> 36:38.044
Something's happening to her
that's triggering her hormones.

36:38.077 --> 36:40.046
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>: The dog has died!
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>: Oh, my God.

36:40.079 --> 36:42.215
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: Oh, my God.
- <font color="#87CEFA">(Chrystal gasps)</font>

36:42.249 --> 36:43.717
He was only just alive.

36:43.749 --> 36:45.151
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHRYSTAL</b></font>:
Kara, hold on to me, baby.

36:45.184 --> 36:46.753
What's happening?

36:46.787 --> 36:49.857
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>:
Who thinks they can swim

36:49.889 --> 36:53.359
a hundred lengths of a pool
against currents

36:53.392 --> 36:56.329
and then turn and swim
an unknown amount

36:56.363 --> 36:58.599
along the coast
till we find another shore?

36:58.631 --> 37:01.034
That's what I'm guessing
the distance is

37:01.066 --> 37:04.104
to swim out
and get around this cove.

37:15.816 --> 37:17.718
It looks too far, babe.

37:17.751 --> 37:20.019
It's not safe.

37:20.052 --> 37:22.021
My name is Brendon.

37:22.055 --> 37:24.525
I went to private school,
my mom is an attorney,

37:24.557 --> 37:27.059
and my dad is a dentist.

37:27.093 --> 37:29.797
- Yo, I just wanted somebody to know that.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: Okay.

37:29.829 --> 37:31.798
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MID-SIZED SEDAN</b></font>:
I have a problem with my blood.

37:31.831 --> 37:33.733
A rare issue with its clotting.

37:33.767 --> 37:36.136
I came to this island
to see the ocean

37:36.168 --> 37:40.239
and remember I'm connected
to something bigger.

37:40.273 --> 37:43.376
That's beautiful, Brendon.

37:43.410 --> 37:44.978
I don't feel the same way

37:45.010 --> 37:46.713
I felt yesterday
or this morning,

37:46.746 --> 37:49.182
and I don't think
my parents would understand.

37:50.182 --> 37:52.485
My thoughts have
more colors in them now.

37:53.854 --> 37:56.890
Yesterday, I had a few colors
and they were really strong,

37:56.923 --> 38:00.327
and now I have more
and they're quieter.

38:00.360 --> 38:02.729
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>PATRICIA</b></font>: Okay!
- <font color="#87CEFA">(clapping)</font>

38:02.762 --> 38:04.765
Everyone, gather!

38:04.798 --> 38:06.834
Come on, come on, come on.

38:06.867 --> 38:09.602
Everyone needs to have
a voice here.

38:09.635 --> 38:11.737
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: Are you sure
we have time for this?

38:11.771 --> 38:13.273
We will make
destructive decisions

38:13.305 --> 38:14.907
if we don't feel safe
with each other.

38:14.941 --> 38:16.743
I know we don't have time,
but...

38:16.776 --> 38:18.946
why don't we start with you two?

38:18.979 --> 38:20.948
Why are you here?

38:23.383 --> 38:25.252
We've been having
a tough time...

38:25.285 --> 38:26.820
Chrystal.

38:26.852 --> 38:28.454
W-We've been going
through something.

38:28.488 --> 38:30.290
He's under a lot of stress
as a doctor.

38:30.322 --> 38:32.091
- He needed some time away.
- Everyone does.

38:32.124 --> 38:34.093
- I'm not unusual in that.
- Charles, it's okay.

38:34.126 --> 38:35.862
I'm not gonna say anything else.

38:35.896 --> 38:37.331
Good!

38:37.363 --> 38:39.332
It's nice to hear from you both.

38:39.365 --> 38:41.367
How about you guys?

38:42.968 --> 38:45.104
<font color="#87CEFA">(Prisca sighs)</font>

38:45.137 --> 38:46.506
Prisca?

38:46.539 --> 38:48.374
It's nothing.

38:48.407 --> 38:50.843
We just have to make a decision.

38:50.876 --> 38:52.979
The kids are reacting
to something.

38:53.012 --> 38:55.882
It's a virus.
It's-it's probably a virus.

38:57.082 --> 38:59.052
I just need to catch my breath.

38:59.084 --> 39:01.121
I just started feeling weird
a minute ago.

39:01.153 --> 39:02.523
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>:
Are you okay, Mom?

39:02.555 --> 39:04.124
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: Mom?
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>: What's wrong?

39:04.157 --> 39:05.825
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>: Um...
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: Are you okay, Mom?

39:05.858 --> 39:07.393
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
I don't think it's the...

39:07.427 --> 39:09.329
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: She has a tumor.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: What?

39:09.361 --> 39:11.331
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: But it's benign. It...
They said it's benign.

39:11.363 --> 39:13.434
- Oh, my God.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: Mom...

39:15.035 --> 39:17.337
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>PATRICIA</b></font>: Wow. Um...
- Is it... Where?

39:17.369 --> 39:18.505
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>:
Mom?

39:18.537 --> 39:19.706
It's okay.

39:19.738 --> 39:21.240
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>:
Can I...

39:21.273 --> 39:23.409
I can feel it.
It's the size of a golf ball.

39:23.443 --> 39:25.812
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>: No, it's supposed
to be three centimeters.

39:25.845 --> 39:27.680
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>:
All right. Let-let me see.

39:27.713 --> 39:29.215
- Whoa, whoa.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: Mom!

39:29.249 --> 39:30.817
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: Prisca.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>PATRICIA</b></font>: She's gonna faint.

39:30.849 --> 39:32.184
- She's gonna faint.
- Wait. - Prisca. - Mom. Mom!

39:32.218 --> 39:34.955
Wake up, Pris. Don't do this.

39:37.389 --> 39:39.559
It's there.

39:39.593 --> 39:42.195
It's been there for a while.
It's the size of a softball.

39:42.227 --> 39:44.097
Jesus.

39:44.130 --> 39:45.532
- It's grown.
- What?

39:45.564 --> 39:47.400
- What's happening to Mom?
- It's okay.

39:47.434 --> 39:49.202
- Trent, it's okay. It's okay.
- Dad.

39:49.235 --> 39:51.204
- What's happening to Mom?
- Trent, why don't you two guys

39:51.236 --> 39:52.905
go play somewhere else
on the beach, okay?

39:52.939 --> 39:54.575
Okay?
Mom's just a little bit tired.

39:54.608 --> 39:56.209
Would you do that for me, tiger?

39:56.242 --> 39:57.611
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PATRICIA</b></font>: The first adult's
being affected.

39:57.644 --> 39:59.246
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
Okay, what if we cut it out?

39:59.278 --> 40:00.746
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: Dad!
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>: Not possible.

40:00.780 --> 40:02.182
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>:
Actually, it is.

40:02.215 --> 40:03.684
- But it's Guy's call.
- No!

40:03.717 --> 40:05.084
No, no, no. No.

40:05.117 --> 40:06.786
I don't want to make
this decision. No.

40:06.820 --> 40:09.022
No, I...

40:09.055 --> 40:11.125
I don't know what to do.

40:15.996 --> 40:17.965
- Do we have alcohol?
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>CHRYSTAL</b></font>: Yes.

40:17.997 --> 40:19.967
Some bottles from the minibar.

40:19.999 --> 40:21.534
I cannot be held responsible.
You understand that, right?

40:21.568 --> 40:23.537
Yes.

40:23.570 --> 40:25.872
Okay. Well, I mean, does anyone
have a needle and thread?

40:25.905 --> 40:27.474
We're gonna have to sew this up.

40:27.506 --> 40:29.108
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PATRICIA</b></font>:
Um, yeah, yeah. Uh...

40:29.142 --> 40:30.877
Here. Here.
Is this the right decision?

40:30.910 --> 40:32.279
Maybe we should all
talk about this.

40:32.311 --> 40:33.313
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
I can't think.

40:33.345 --> 40:35.081
This tumor is going to kill her.

40:40.086 --> 40:44.457
Did you know that Jack Nicholson
did a film with Marlon Brando?

40:44.490 --> 40:45.693
Oh, no.

40:46.693 --> 40:47.995
What is he saying?

40:48.028 --> 40:49.463
Wh-What was the name
of that film?

40:49.496 --> 40:51.064
- Charles, breathe.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>: Are you okay?

40:51.097 --> 40:52.466
Yes.

40:52.499 --> 40:54.067
Will you just let me
do my job, please?

40:54.099 --> 40:55.468
Is he okay?

41:17.189 --> 41:18.958
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>:
Cut her again.

41:18.992 --> 41:21.028
We'll keep our hands in there
to keep the incision open.

41:21.061 --> 41:23.130
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MID-SIZED SEDAN</b></font>:
Guy, I can help, brother.

41:23.162 --> 41:24.865
No. No, I'll take care of her.

41:24.898 --> 41:26.499
Does anyone know
the name of that film?

41:26.532 --> 41:28.934
It was with Jack Nicholson...

41:28.968 --> 41:31.138
and Marlon Brando.

41:31.171 --> 41:32.539
Both!

41:32.572 --> 41:34.106
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>:
Try again, Doctor.

41:34.139 --> 41:36.308
Oblique incision
on the side of the belly.

41:36.342 --> 41:38.177
Four to six inches.
You can do this.

41:40.880 --> 41:43.050
Put your fingers
inside the incision.

41:43.082 --> 41:44.684
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
Okay.

41:44.718 --> 41:46.654
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>: Can you open it
a little wider, please?

41:47.686 --> 41:49.488
It's closing around my fingers.

41:49.521 --> 41:51.190
Keep pulling it apart.

41:51.224 --> 41:52.793
That's it.

41:52.825 --> 41:55.361
I'm lifting the tumor out.

41:55.394 --> 41:57.030
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>:
Wow!

41:57.063 --> 41:58.664
<font color="#87CEFA">(chuckling)</font>
It's the size of a cantaloupe.

41:58.697 --> 42:00.466
W-Wait.

42:00.499 --> 42:02.802
It's attached to something.

42:02.836 --> 42:04.004
Muscle tissue.

42:04.037 --> 42:05.706
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>:
Okay. You, um,

42:05.738 --> 42:08.541
hold the incision open
a little wider, if you would.

42:09.675 --> 42:11.343
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
I'm so sorry, Pris.

42:11.376 --> 42:13.846
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>: Just cutting
underneath the tumor.

42:15.247 --> 42:17.284
Okay. Got it.

42:29.628 --> 42:31.964
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>:
Mom. <font color="#87CEFA">(whimpers)</font>

42:32.965 --> 42:34.767
Prisca?

42:35.769 --> 42:37.504
Mom?

42:37.537 --> 42:39.406
<font color="#87CEFA">(crying)</font>

42:53.285 --> 42:55.554
It's okay.

42:55.588 --> 42:57.457
I just fainted.

42:59.425 --> 43:01.227
We took the tumor out.

43:01.260 --> 43:03.262
It was going to kill you.

43:04.296 --> 43:07.900
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>: Your husband made
a fast decision.

43:19.244 --> 43:21.347
Guy, I feel better.

43:30.823 --> 43:32.860
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

43:41.800 --> 43:43.636
Damn.

43:45.204 --> 43:47.039
Come on, y'all, look at this!

43:48.974 --> 43:50.643
Hurry!

43:53.213 --> 43:55.582
Damn.

43:55.615 --> 43:57.651
Come on, y'all.

44:05.959 --> 44:08.428
Can we all agree
I didn't do that?

44:08.461 --> 44:10.030
What happened to her?

44:10.063 --> 44:12.365
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
The body has decomposed.

44:12.398 --> 44:14.700
- How quickly can that happen?
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>: A long time.

44:14.733 --> 44:16.335
Mom knows this stuff.

44:16.369 --> 44:18.671
I'm not a forensic pathologist,

44:18.704 --> 44:21.207
but from excavations
for the museum,

44:21.240 --> 44:24.476
I know that it varies
based on soil and temperature.

44:24.510 --> 44:27.479
My best guess... an exposed body,

44:27.512 --> 44:31.684
the flesh will be gone
in approximately seven years.

44:31.718 --> 44:33.687
And this happened in what,
three hours?

44:33.720 --> 44:35.121
I know.

44:35.153 --> 44:37.056
And bones, we found,
will disintegrate

44:37.090 --> 44:39.025
in 30 years more.

44:39.057 --> 44:40.793
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MID-SIZED SEDAN</b></font>:
The hell, man?

44:40.827 --> 44:42.829
On this beach, less than
20 hours after you die,

44:42.861 --> 44:44.497
you just return to dust.

44:45.530 --> 44:47.066
What exactly are we saying?

44:47.099 --> 44:49.201
Something is going on
with time on this beach.

44:49.235 --> 44:50.838
Time?

44:56.675 --> 44:58.611
You have wrinkles.

45:00.613 --> 45:03.050
<font color="#87CEFA">(rustling)</font>

45:08.755 --> 45:11.892
<font color="#87CEFA">(chewing, food crunching)</font>

45:11.925 --> 45:13.861
<font color="#8B814C"><b>KARA</b></font>:
I'm scared.

45:17.597 --> 45:21.501
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: It's best to focus
on specifics in the present

45:21.534 --> 45:23.336
in unsettling situations.

45:23.369 --> 45:24.571
<font color="#8B814C"><b>KARA</b></font>:
Mm-hmm.

45:24.604 --> 45:25.839
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
Like breathing.

45:25.872 --> 45:27.274
<font color="#87CEFA">(Trent takes deep breath)</font>

45:27.307 --> 45:29.843
<font color="#8B814C"><b>KARA</b></font>:
What's happening to us?

45:29.876 --> 45:31.410
Are we sick, too?

45:31.443 --> 45:32.912
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
No, I don't think so.

45:32.945 --> 45:35.381
I think we're just growing.

45:35.414 --> 45:37.851
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>: Going by
Trent and Maddox's ages

45:37.883 --> 45:39.852
and the time we spent
on this beach,

45:39.885 --> 45:42.354
half an hour is equivalent

45:42.387 --> 45:45.090
to something like one year
of our lives.

45:45.124 --> 45:46.760
This must be true for all of us.

45:46.793 --> 45:48.695
We just don't see it
on everyone.

45:48.727 --> 45:50.296
You know, it's the first time

45:50.329 --> 45:52.131
- they wished they were Black.
- Mm-hmm.

45:52.164 --> 45:54.534
The kids are eating so much
because their mass is growing.

45:54.566 --> 45:58.537
They need to grow an enormous
amount of mass quickly.

45:58.570 --> 46:00.706
We're staying roughly
the same mass.

46:00.740 --> 46:02.742
Our cells are just aging.

46:02.775 --> 46:05.144
<font color="#8B814C"><b>KARA</b></font>:
I don't feel the same.

46:05.177 --> 46:08.113
It's like my mind
is changing, too.

46:08.146 --> 46:11.250
I'm getting many thoughts
at the same time.

46:12.251 --> 46:13.954
It's weird.

46:17.590 --> 46:20.459
I'm not as scared about
what's happening to us.

46:21.427 --> 46:23.496
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
What about our hair and nails?

46:23.528 --> 46:26.265
Shouldn't they be growing
at an abnormal rate?

46:26.298 --> 46:28.668
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>: Maybe it has to do
with the fact that the cells

46:28.700 --> 46:30.637
in hair and nails are dead

46:30.669 --> 46:33.106
and they aren't reacting
in the same way.

46:33.139 --> 46:36.476
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MID-SIZED SEDAN</b></font>: On this beach,
60 minutes is two years.

46:36.508 --> 46:40.780
We'll age almost 50 years
in one day here.

46:40.813 --> 46:43.450
Almost a lifetime.

46:43.483 --> 46:46.119
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

46:46.151 --> 46:48.956
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>: I think it could be the
rock that surrounds this beach.

46:50.490 --> 46:52.959
If our cells are being affected,

46:52.992 --> 46:56.528
speeding up in their processes,

46:56.561 --> 46:59.365
then us trying to leave is like

46:59.398 --> 47:03.168
swimming to the surface too fast
after being deep in the ocean.

47:03.202 --> 47:06.039
Our bodies can't reacclimate.

47:06.072 --> 47:08.976
That's why we go unconscious
when we try to leave.

47:10.510 --> 47:12.678
Maybe...

47:12.711 --> 47:16.315
we could slowly walk
through the canyon.

47:16.349 --> 47:19.452
Take a step, stand still.

47:19.485 --> 47:23.456
Do it over eight to ten hours.

47:23.488 --> 47:25.525
Let our bodies acclimate.

47:27.325 --> 47:29.695
But according to
Prisca's timeline,

47:29.729 --> 47:32.499
who would be willing to give up
20 years of their life trying?

47:32.532 --> 47:34.467
I'm sorry, this is nonsense.

47:34.499 --> 47:36.736
Let's not shut down
everyone's experience.

47:37.736 --> 47:39.238
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
Wait. Where are the kids?

47:43.175 --> 47:44.410
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
Trent!

47:44.443 --> 47:45.744
Kara!

47:45.778 --> 47:48.048
Answer us now!

47:48.081 --> 47:49.381
We need you here!

47:49.414 --> 47:50.750
There they are.

48:05.064 --> 48:07.868
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>KARA</b></font>: Want some?
- No, I'm not hungry.

48:24.717 --> 48:26.419
Hey.

48:26.452 --> 48:28.388
Mom! Dad!

48:31.791 --> 48:33.827
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

48:45.403 --> 48:47.273
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHRYSTAL</b></font>:
Kara?

48:47.305 --> 48:49.208
What did you do?

48:49.242 --> 48:51.044
We were just playing. It's okay.

48:51.077 --> 48:52.412
I just got a little fat.

48:52.445 --> 48:53.847
Mom, you're better.

48:55.648 --> 48:57.617
- Maddox?
- <font color="#87CEFA">(Maddox scoffs)</font>

48:57.650 --> 48:59.052
Maddox.

48:59.084 --> 49:00.352
It's okay, Trent.

49:01.419 --> 49:04.291
Just let Mom and Dad
figure this out.

49:06.791 --> 49:09.496
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
My God, Guy.

49:09.528 --> 49:11.264
It's okay, right, Mom?

49:11.296 --> 49:15.267
Jack Nicholson and Marlon Brando

49:15.300 --> 49:17.903
were in a movie together.

49:17.936 --> 49:20.339
If she walked into
the emergency room,

49:20.372 --> 49:23.142
I'd say she's about
five months pregnant.

49:23.175 --> 49:24.744
- What?
- <font color="#87CEFA">(laughing)</font> What?

49:24.776 --> 49:26.479
Just stay calm, Trent.

49:26.512 --> 49:29.015
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>: She'll only be pregnant
for about 20 minutes

49:29.048 --> 49:30.683
from the time of conception.

49:30.715 --> 49:32.084
Why do you keep looking at me

49:32.117 --> 49:33.452
like you want
to steal my wallet?

49:33.485 --> 49:35.121
Do you want me
to punch you in the face?

49:35.153 --> 49:36.588
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>:
Calm down.

49:36.622 --> 49:38.091
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

49:38.124 --> 49:40.959
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>: All right.
Let's just concentrate

49:40.992 --> 49:42.928
on the issue at hand.

49:42.961 --> 49:44.664
Do you know about movies?

49:44.697 --> 49:46.666
Dad, Mom tells you to sit down
when you get like this.

49:46.698 --> 49:48.767
Okay, we need to get her help.

49:48.800 --> 49:50.702
Okay? This cannot happen here.

49:50.735 --> 49:52.271
- It's gotten bigger.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>: Kara.

49:52.305 --> 49:54.307
- It's Kara, right?
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>CHRYSTAL</b></font>: Yeah.

49:54.340 --> 49:56.543
- Lay down on a blanket.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>PATRICIA</b></font>: It's gonna be okay.

49:56.575 --> 49:58.544
There's a lot of people here
that can help you.

49:58.577 --> 50:00.112
We're all like your family now.

50:00.146 --> 50:02.715
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHRYSTAL</b></font>:
Oh, God. <font color="#87CEFA">(whimpers)</font>

50:02.747 --> 50:04.784
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: Our cells are aging
very fast here.

50:04.816 --> 50:07.019
Something to do with the rocks
around the beach, we think.

50:07.052 --> 50:08.654
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>: Just lay down
on the sand. Okay.

50:08.688 --> 50:10.122
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: Whatever would have
happened to us

50:10.155 --> 50:11.724
is happening to us really fast.

50:11.756 --> 50:13.226
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
Okay.

50:13.258 --> 50:14.827
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: What you did is
how babies are made.

50:14.860 --> 50:16.628
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: I know, but I thought
you had to do that

50:16.662 --> 50:18.497
ten times or something.

50:18.530 --> 50:20.233
Did I get that wrong?

50:20.265 --> 50:22.534
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: Look, it can happen
after only once.

50:22.568 --> 50:24.236
<font color="#87CEFA">(Kara whimpering)</font>

50:24.269 --> 50:26.171
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: We didn't get a chance
to talk about all this.

50:26.204 --> 50:28.207
Are Trent and I having a baby?

50:28.240 --> 50:29.909
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
Did I get it wrong?

50:29.941 --> 50:32.177
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>: Only a couple
of minutes left if we're right.

50:32.211 --> 50:34.180
- Is that the baby?
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>: You got it. Okay.

50:34.213 --> 50:35.715
- Mom.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>CHRYSTAL</b></font>: Charles!

50:35.747 --> 50:37.182
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>: Kara?
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>: I...

50:37.215 --> 50:38.650
I need to think about
what to do.

50:38.684 --> 50:40.753
- Mom, I think I...
- No. I need to help her.

50:40.785 --> 50:41.988
Mom!

50:42.021 --> 50:43.323
- I'm scared!
- It's okay.

50:43.356 --> 50:44.991
- Kara. - Wait.
- Mom, it's coming.

50:45.023 --> 50:46.391
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>:
Stay with me. Stay with me.

50:46.425 --> 50:48.160
Come on, baby.

50:48.193 --> 50:50.095
- Can you hold her hand? Kara?
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: I've decided...

50:50.128 --> 50:52.431
I'm gonna marry her, and we are
never gonna yell at each other,

50:52.465 --> 50:54.200
and we are never
getting divorced!

50:54.233 --> 50:56.401
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>: Trent, listen to me.
She's going to feel pain.

50:56.434 --> 50:58.403
Intense pain. Okay?

50:58.436 --> 51:00.105
Like she never felt before.

51:00.139 --> 51:02.008
But then it's going to pass.

51:02.041 --> 51:04.443
- Okay? It's going to pass.
- <font color="#87CEFA">(Trent sobbing)</font>

51:04.477 --> 51:06.412
<font color="#87CEFA">(Kara wailing)</font>

51:06.445 --> 51:09.115
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: Chrystal.
- <font color="#87CEFA">(Kara screams)</font>

51:09.148 --> 51:11.718
Chrystal!

51:11.751 --> 51:13.919
Hey, you blacked out.

51:13.952 --> 51:16.456
You can't go that way.

51:16.488 --> 51:18.291
Come on. You're okay now.

51:18.323 --> 51:20.026
Come on.

51:20.059 --> 51:21.427
- Get up.
- <font color="#87CEFA">(baby crying)</font>

51:21.459 --> 51:23.095
Come here.

51:23.128 --> 51:25.197
Look.

51:25.231 --> 51:27.499
<font color="#87CEFA">(Chrystal whimpers, chuckles)</font>

51:29.901 --> 51:32.405
You're okay. Come on. Come on.

51:32.438 --> 51:34.439
- Babies crying helps them breathe.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: It's here.

51:34.472 --> 51:36.375
We looked that up,
remember, Mom?

51:36.409 --> 51:38.278
<font color="#87CEFA">(Trent chuckles)</font>

51:40.146 --> 51:42.481
- <font color="#87CEFA">(crying stops)</font>
- <font color="#87CEFA">(gasping)</font>

51:48.119 --> 51:50.389
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PATRICIA</b></font>: We put him
on the towel to clean him up.

51:50.423 --> 51:53.959
He looked around
and closed his eyes.

51:53.992 --> 51:56.996
We had him on the towel
for one minute.

51:57.028 --> 51:58.997
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHRYSTAL</b></font>:
He died from lack of attention.

51:59.030 --> 52:00.999
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MID-SIZED SEDAN</b></font>:
Things are moving too fast here

52:01.032 --> 52:03.168
for a baby to survive.

52:03.202 --> 52:05.305
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
No. No, you're lying.

52:05.338 --> 52:07.006
You're lying! You're all lying!

52:07.039 --> 52:08.841
- Trent. Shut up, Trent!
- You're lying! You're lying!

52:08.874 --> 52:11.511
- You're lying!
- Hey, hey, hey.

52:11.543 --> 52:13.445
<font color="#87CEFA">(Trent sobbing)</font>

52:13.479 --> 52:16.716
Maybe we should all talk
about what just happened.

52:19.385 --> 52:21.153
<font color="#87CEFA">(sobbing)</font>
Charles.

52:21.186 --> 52:22.988
- Get us out of here!
- TRENT: <font color="#87CEFA">(sobs)</font> It's my baby.

52:23.021 --> 52:24.756
Get us out of here now!

52:24.789 --> 52:26.793
You were supposed to protect us!

52:26.825 --> 52:28.994
You didn't protect us!

52:29.028 --> 52:31.631
Kara's hurt!

52:31.664 --> 52:33.932
I will make these decisions.

52:33.965 --> 52:35.868
Just give me a second.

52:38.236 --> 52:40.539
<font color="#87CEFA">(Chrystal screams, sobs)</font>

52:40.572 --> 52:42.275
I used to see you
in our neighborhood.

52:42.307 --> 52:44.010
Who... who are you?

52:44.043 --> 52:45.378
<font color="#87CEFA">(knife thumping in sand)</font>

52:45.410 --> 52:47.380
I'm Jarin!

52:49.048 --> 52:51.217
<font color="#87CEFA">(crying)</font>
I-I don't know where you live.

52:54.019 --> 52:56.022
Don't condescend to me.

52:58.890 --> 53:01.327
Put some makeup on your face.

53:05.898 --> 53:07.934
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

53:20.012 --> 53:22.615
I'm sorry about the baby.

53:24.582 --> 53:27.619
When I was your age,
I was in love with a man.

53:29.521 --> 53:31.557
His name was Giuseppe.

53:32.858 --> 53:35.762
He wasn't very handsome,
and I left him.

53:37.128 --> 53:40.366
We looked silly together,
he and I.

53:41.367 --> 53:43.403
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

53:49.608 --> 53:51.544
He had nothing to offer.

53:54.380 --> 53:57.282
For some reason,
I think about him a lot here.

54:04.055 --> 54:06.291
<font color="#87CEFA">(sniffles, shudders)</font>

54:07.827 --> 54:09.729
Leave me alone.

54:10.896 --> 54:12.631
<font color="#87CEFA">(screaming)</font>

54:13.765 --> 54:15.267
<font color="#87CEFA">(screaming)</font>

54:15.300 --> 54:18.337
- <font color="#87CEFA">(grunting)</font>
- <font color="#87CEFA">(knife striking repeatedly)</font>

54:21.307 --> 54:23.943
Charles, stop!

54:23.976 --> 54:26.746
Stop! Stop!

54:37.088 --> 54:39.157
- He's gone.
- <font color="#87CEFA">(Chrystal whimpers)</font>

54:39.191 --> 54:40.959
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHRYSTAL</b></font>:
Oh, God.

54:40.992 --> 54:43.028
<font color="#87CEFA">(Maddox sobbing)</font>

54:46.131 --> 54:48.168
<font color="#87CEFA">(Maddox and Chrystal sobbing)</font>

54:51.637 --> 54:54.240
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>: Bring your bag.
Okay, come here.

54:54.273 --> 54:56.443
<font color="#87CEFA">(sobbing continues)</font>

55:04.983 --> 55:07.519
I'm just going to take it...

55:12.490 --> 55:14.494
- ...now.
- It's okay.

55:14.526 --> 55:17.030
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>:
Everything will be okay.

55:28.374 --> 55:30.410
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

55:35.680 --> 55:38.284
<font color="#8B814C"><b>JARIN</b></font>: I'll find another beach,
and I'll try to find help.

55:38.316 --> 55:39.684
<font color="#87CEFA">(Prisca crying)</font>

55:39.718 --> 55:41.621
She needs her medicine.

55:41.653 --> 55:43.456
We're lucky she hasn't
had a seizure yet.

55:43.488 --> 55:46.325
It must be the beach,
whatever it's doing to my body.

55:47.559 --> 55:50.063
Guy, I was on the swim team.
I'll make it.

55:52.064 --> 55:53.600
I'll make it.

55:59.939 --> 56:01.608
Watch him.

56:15.921 --> 56:18.558
<font color="#87CEFA">(wind howling)</font>

56:18.590 --> 56:21.026
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
Maybe I could climb that rock.

56:22.126 --> 56:24.229
Maybe the effect,
the blacking out,

56:24.262 --> 56:26.531
doesn't happen if you go up.

56:26.564 --> 56:28.601
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
You can't do it.

56:28.633 --> 56:30.535
- I'll do it.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>CHRYSTAL</b></font>: Yeah, he's strong.

56:30.568 --> 56:32.371
- He can do it. He can do it.
- Yeah.

56:32.403 --> 56:34.840
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>: No. I won't allow
my son to do that.

56:34.872 --> 56:36.508
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PATRICIA</b></font>: Prisca's right.
It's too dangerous.

56:36.541 --> 56:38.209
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
It's a last resort.

56:38.242 --> 56:41.012
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHARLES</b></font>:
Mom...

56:41.046 --> 56:45.384
I do feel overwhelmed.

56:45.416 --> 56:49.354
I'm managing,
but no one must know.

56:49.387 --> 56:52.223
<font color="#87CEFA">(crunching)</font>

56:52.256 --> 56:55.293
They'll try to stop me
from working.

56:55.327 --> 56:58.030
What should I do?

56:58.063 --> 57:00.666
Mom, tell me what to do.

57:02.468 --> 57:05.705
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: Prisca,
something's bothering me.

57:05.738 --> 57:09.275
Charles' family knew he had
some kind of mental disorder.

57:09.307 --> 57:12.210
Someone in each group was sick.

57:12.244 --> 57:14.213
How did you first hear
about this place?

57:14.246 --> 57:16.715
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
I don't know. I-I fell upon it.

57:16.749 --> 57:18.317
A random sweepstakes.

57:18.349 --> 57:20.652
It came with a receipt
at the pharmacy.

57:20.686 --> 57:23.488
I just followed it up online,
started getting emails.

57:23.521 --> 57:25.323
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: They know
our medical condition.

57:25.356 --> 57:27.293
They chose us.

57:27.325 --> 57:28.961
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
They have our passports.

57:28.994 --> 57:30.762
We could just disappear.

57:30.796 --> 57:33.232
They sent us a special car
to the airport.

57:33.264 --> 57:35.000
- A plane.
- They can...

57:35.034 --> 57:38.303
They can make it look like
we never left our house.

57:46.979 --> 57:49.015
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

57:53.151 --> 57:56.588
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: You were thinking
about leaving Dad,

57:56.622 --> 57:59.058
weren't you?

58:05.197 --> 58:07.066
Yes.

58:08.400 --> 58:10.869
I didn't want you two to suffer.

58:14.639 --> 58:16.675
Was there someone else?

58:27.686 --> 58:29.722
Did Dad know?

58:40.932 --> 58:43.235
Maddox.

58:43.267 --> 58:45.470
Please.

58:45.503 --> 58:48.239
I found out about this tumor,

58:48.273 --> 58:50.575
and I got scared.

58:50.608 --> 58:54.345
I stare at the remains of
nameless people in glass cases,

58:54.378 --> 58:57.482
and I kept thinking I'm going
to be one of those people.

58:57.515 --> 58:59.218
Does that make any sense?

59:00.952 --> 59:04.724
I feel different
than I felt yesterday.

59:06.592 --> 59:09.028
What I did feels like
an illusion.

59:09.061 --> 59:10.530
I swear.

59:12.731 --> 59:14.867
Do you hate me now?

59:16.901 --> 59:19.639
I just need some time, Mom.

59:25.244 --> 59:27.447
We don't have that, baby.

59:29.747 --> 59:31.784
Look at you.

59:34.418 --> 59:36.455
You're an adult.

59:39.157 --> 59:41.626
Be strong for everyone.

59:45.963 --> 59:48.433
Connect to something bigger.

59:54.072 --> 59:56.108
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

01:00:14.626 --> 01:00:16.662
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

01:00:27.005 --> 01:00:29.709
<font color="#87CEFA">(screaming)</font>

01:00:44.789 --> 01:00:46.825
<font color="#87CEFA">(whimpering, gasping)</font>

01:00:48.059 --> 01:00:49.360
Here, here. Dad.

01:00:49.394 --> 01:00:51.330
Lay him down. Lay him down.

01:00:55.467 --> 01:00:57.503
<font color="#87CEFA">(sobbing)</font>

01:01:11.383 --> 01:01:14.453
<font color="#87CEFA">(Patricia sobbing)</font>

01:01:14.485 --> 01:01:16.988
He must have gone
unconscious swimming.

01:01:19.358 --> 01:01:21.861
Brendon didn't do anything
to that woman.

01:01:22.860 --> 01:01:25.597
We can't swim out, Prisca.

01:01:34.171 --> 01:01:37.008
We're not getting
off this beach.

01:01:38.010 --> 01:01:41.847
We never had a prom.

01:01:41.880 --> 01:01:43.414
Or a graduation.

01:01:43.447 --> 01:01:46.251
There are so many memories
we didn't have.

01:01:48.119 --> 01:01:50.021
It's not fair.

01:01:54.226 --> 01:01:56.262
He needs to rest now.

01:02:02.367 --> 01:02:04.403
<font color="#87CEFA">(quiet rattling)</font>

01:02:07.238 --> 01:02:09.275
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

01:02:27.758 --> 01:02:29.794
<font color="#87CEFA">(quiet rattling)</font>

01:02:31.630 --> 01:02:33.398
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
Kara.

01:02:35.800 --> 01:02:37.436
Kara.

01:02:38.669 --> 01:02:40.438
Wait. What if you get
dizzy up there?

01:02:40.472 --> 01:02:42.608
- You might black out.
- Trent, we are in charge now.

01:02:42.640 --> 01:02:44.443
My dad could hurt more people.

01:02:44.476 --> 01:02:46.378
I have to get him
off this beach.

01:02:46.410 --> 01:02:48.380
Kara! Don't climb that.

01:02:48.412 --> 01:02:49.981
Come down!

01:02:50.014 --> 01:02:52.083
We'll find another way.

01:02:52.117 --> 01:02:54.285
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>: No, don't! Trent.
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: Listen to Mom.

01:02:54.318 --> 01:02:55.820
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
I have to go with her!

01:02:55.854 --> 01:02:57.656
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
Kara, wait! Don't climb!

01:02:57.689 --> 01:02:59.124
Let me get your mother!

01:02:59.157 --> 01:03:00.559
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: Kara!
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>: It's not the way.

01:03:00.592 --> 01:03:02.294
She's panicked and desperate.

01:03:02.327 --> 01:03:03.996
Talk to each other.

01:03:04.028 --> 01:03:07.565
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: Kara, you and I
should just stay together.

01:03:07.599 --> 01:03:09.133
What if we spend
this whole time trying

01:03:09.166 --> 01:03:10.735
to get out of here
and we still don't make it?

01:03:10.769 --> 01:03:12.638
<font color="#87CEFA">(wind whistling)</font>

01:03:12.671 --> 01:03:14.740
It'll be too short
if we don't try.

01:03:14.773 --> 01:03:16.307
No, Kara, please!

01:03:16.340 --> 01:03:18.376
Please just stay with me,
please.

01:03:20.012 --> 01:03:22.048
<font color="#87CEFA">(wind whistling)</font>

01:03:24.349 --> 01:03:26.117
<font color="#87CEFA">(whimpers)</font>

01:03:27.552 --> 01:03:29.287
<font color="#87CEFA">(wind whistling)</font>

01:03:29.320 --> 01:03:30.956
<font color="#87CEFA">(grunting)</font>

01:03:33.291 --> 01:03:36.294
If she makes it to the ledge,
she might have a chance.

01:03:37.863 --> 01:03:39.832
Go to the ledge and rest!

01:03:39.865 --> 01:03:41.968
- <font color="#87CEFA">(wind whistling)</font>
- <font color="#87CEFA">(grunting)</font>

01:03:44.869 --> 01:03:47.205
There has to be a way out.

01:03:47.238 --> 01:03:50.543
It's a mathematical certainty
there must be a way out.

01:03:53.811 --> 01:03:55.847
<font color="#87CEFA">(panting)</font>

01:04:01.385 --> 01:04:02.653
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
No. Why is she stopping?

01:04:02.686 --> 01:04:03.722
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
No.

01:04:05.856 --> 01:04:08.293
No. Kara! Kara, wake up!

01:04:08.325 --> 01:04:09.827
Kara, wake up!

01:04:09.860 --> 01:04:11.429
Wake up!

01:04:14.733 --> 01:04:16.168
<font color="#87CEFA">(gasps)</font>

01:04:22.106 --> 01:04:24.043
<font color="#87CEFA">(breath trembling)</font>

01:04:28.947 --> 01:04:31.416
<font color="#87CEFA">(sobbing)</font>

01:04:45.430 --> 01:04:47.700
<font color="#87CEFA">(whimpering)</font>

01:04:55.407 --> 01:04:57.075
Kara.

01:04:58.809 --> 01:05:00.880
<font color="#87CEFA">(whimpering)</font>

01:05:02.581 --> 01:05:04.617
<font color="#87CEFA">(sobbing)</font>
Daddy.

01:05:07.718 --> 01:05:09.755
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

01:05:23.168 --> 01:05:25.604
Let's all stay together.

01:05:25.637 --> 01:05:28.640
Nobody in this family
goes alone anywhere.

01:05:30.142 --> 01:05:31.944
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PATRICIA</b></font>:
I think I figured it out.

01:05:31.977 --> 01:05:35.014
I'm using these to swim out.

01:05:38.983 --> 01:05:40.952
I have a sister.

01:05:40.985 --> 01:05:42.420
She's a therapist, too.

01:05:42.454 --> 01:05:44.555
I need to get to my sister.

01:05:44.588 --> 01:05:46.924
We never talk.
We had a fight a long time ago.

01:05:46.957 --> 01:05:50.262
She's older, but now I am.

01:05:51.496 --> 01:05:54.200
The fighting seems
ridiculous now.

01:05:59.204 --> 01:06:00.839
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
Patricia.

01:06:00.872 --> 01:06:02.441
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
Patricia.

01:06:02.474 --> 01:06:03.842
<font color="#87CEFA">(grunting rapidly)</font>

01:06:03.874 --> 01:06:05.244
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
No.

01:06:05.276 --> 01:06:06.845
Wh-What's happening to her?

01:06:06.878 --> 01:06:08.247
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
What's going on?

01:06:08.280 --> 01:06:10.082
She was fine.
What-what's happening?

01:06:10.115 --> 01:06:12.485
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: She keeps
stopping and starting.

01:06:14.452 --> 01:06:15.486
<font color="#87CEFA">(gasps)</font>

01:06:15.519 --> 01:06:18.657
No. Dad, do something.

01:06:31.235 --> 01:06:32.737
<font color="#87CEFA">(Prisca whimpers softly)</font>

01:06:38.642 --> 01:06:40.880
<font color="#87CEFA">(Prisca sobbing)</font>

01:07:00.264 --> 01:07:02.333
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

01:07:07.905 --> 01:07:09.941
Oh, no.

01:07:11.209 --> 01:07:13.044
<font color="#8B814C"><b>CHRYSTAL</b></font>:
Kara?

01:07:14.912 --> 01:07:17.582
Kara, where are you?

01:07:21.052 --> 01:07:24.423
Somebody's done this
to us, Kara.

01:07:27.025 --> 01:07:30.329
I can't protect you anymore.

01:07:30.361 --> 01:07:32.363
Kara!

01:07:32.396 --> 01:07:34.432
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

01:07:40.572 --> 01:07:42.374
<font color="#87CEFA">(waves crashing)</font>

01:07:42.407 --> 01:07:43.941
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
No, you don't know.

01:07:43.974 --> 01:07:45.743
Jarin went in a different way.

01:07:45.776 --> 01:07:47.612
He went on, and I... and I'm
a better swimmer than he is.

01:07:47.646 --> 01:07:49.948
He's older than me.
I-I can probably swim...

01:07:49.981 --> 01:07:52.517
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
Trent, stop it. No. No.

01:07:52.550 --> 01:07:54.785
No, you're not
a better swimmer than him.

01:07:54.818 --> 01:07:56.220
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
Yeah, but let me try.

01:07:56.253 --> 01:07:58.089
<font color="#8B814C"><b>GUY</b></font>:
Listen. Listen.

01:07:58.122 --> 01:08:00.626
<font color="#87CEFA">(conversation continues,
muffled)</font>

01:08:00.659 --> 01:08:03.428
<font color="#87CEFA">(all sounds fade to silence)</font>

01:08:12.137 --> 01:08:14.773
- <font color="#87CEFA">(sound returns)</font>
- <font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: We're not gonna let you.

01:08:14.805 --> 01:08:16.974
Stop. It won't work.

01:08:17.008 --> 01:08:18.743
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>:
Well, I don't want to give up.

01:08:18.777 --> 01:08:20.212
- I really don't want to give up.
- We're not giving up.

01:08:20.245 --> 01:08:21.747
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: And I think,
if you let me try...

01:08:21.779 --> 01:08:24.116
<font color="#87CEFA">(chatter continues indistinctly
in distance)</font>

01:08:39.263 --> 01:08:41.064
CHRYSTAL: <font color="#87CEFA">(crying)</font>
My back.

01:08:41.098 --> 01:08:42.933
I need my calcium.

01:08:42.966 --> 01:08:44.769
<font color="#8B814C"><b>PRISCA</b></font>:
Chrystal?

01:08:44.803 --> 01:08:47.171
Chrystal, stay with us.

01:08:47.205 --> 01:08:49.207
Don't look at me.

01:09:06.825 --> 01:09:10.028
Prisca, I have to
tell you something.

01:09:15.567 --> 01:09:18.170
I saw your text messages
one day.

01:09:18.202 --> 01:09:20.238
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

01:09:22.906 --> 01:09:25.176
He says romantic things.

01:09:31.383 --> 01:09:33.218
I'm sorry.

01:09:37.054 --> 01:09:40.157
I don't know who I would have
been okay with, but...

01:09:40.191 --> 01:09:42.060
with that guy?

01:09:44.696 --> 01:09:46.465
He's-he's a joke.

01:09:46.497 --> 01:09:49.067
He's a pretend person.

01:09:49.099 --> 01:09:51.769
You deserve someone
so much better than that.

01:09:54.272 --> 01:09:56.475
I should have said something
when I saw it.

01:09:56.508 --> 01:09:59.211
I hide from everything.
I'm a fucking coward.

01:09:59.244 --> 01:10:03.014
This was no one's
responsibility but me.

01:10:03.046 --> 01:10:06.451
Your anger should be aimed
at me, just me.

01:10:13.724 --> 01:10:18.062
There's no place
I want to be but with you.

01:10:19.863 --> 01:10:22.300
Do you believe me?

01:10:24.369 --> 01:10:26.237
I want to be here...

01:10:30.040 --> 01:10:31.909
...right now.

01:10:38.249 --> 01:10:40.285
<font color="#FF9966"> <i>♫  ♫</i> </font>

01:10:48.492 --> 01:10:50.562
<font color="#87CEFA">(rustling)</font>

01:10:52.330 --> 01:10:54.299
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>:
It's notebooks.

01:10:54.331 --> 01:10:56.401
<font color="#87CEFA">(wind whistling)</font>

01:10:58.135 --> 01:11:01.106
<font color="#8B814C"><b>TRENT</b></font>: Well, maybe we can use
some of the empty pages

01:11:01.138 --> 01:11:03.775
for the fire,
keep Mom and Dad warm.

01:11:07.978 --> 01:11:10.781
<font color="#8B814C"><b>MADDOX</b></font>: Whoever it was wanted
